      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "d96c38aa85d80f5e0630c28d242f8279987c8d5e",
            "subject": "LU-6719 osd-zfs: Ignore EEXIST during object init"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-01-18 19:54:46.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-02-05 15:07:03.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6587 obdclass: use OBD_FREE_LARGE with OBD_ALLOC_LARGE",
        "message": "LU-6587 obdclass: use OBD_FREE_LARGE with OBD_ALLOC_LARGE\n\nThe change to use is_vmalloc_addr() instead of checking the allocation\nsize was introduced in commit 919b85d796f8, which allows using trying\nkmalloc() before vmalloc(), but the deprecation of OBD_FREE_LARGE()\nshould not have happened since this adds needless overhead.\n\nUse OBD_FREE_LARGE() for memory allocated with OBD_ALLOC_LARGE() so\nthat we only need to check is_vmalloc_addr() in OBD_FREE_LARGE()\ninstead of every call to OBD_FREE().\n\nAdd comments to data structures using OBD_ALLOC_LARGE() memory so\nthat it is clear to the users that OBD_FREE_LARGE() must be used\nwhen freeing that memory.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ief38142f6f777eec4ec0dae4ec64bfbf78b804ed\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/18034\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Yang Sheng <yang.sheng@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
